Computer Science 50
Problem Set 3


Q.1 Besides 4 × 4 (which are Game of Fifteen’s dimensions), what other dimensions does the framework allow?

Ans. Besides 4 × 4 (which are Game of Fifteen’s dimensions), 3x3 , 5x5 , .... , 9x9 dimensions are allowed by the framework.

Q.2 With what sort of data structure is the game’s board represented?

Ans. The game’s board is represented by a matrix ( array of array board[][] ) data structure.

Q.3 What function is called to greet the player at game’s start?

Ans. greet() function is called to greet the player at game’s start.

Q.4 What functions do you apparently need to implement?

Ans. I need to implement init, draw, move, won functions .